DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nCost: Fre
 e\\nAges: 0-60 months\\nCategory: Play & Games\\n\\nJoin us for a free eve
 ning where children and caretakers are invited to play in a sensory-friend
 ly\, neuro-affirming environment! We encourage the whole family to attend\
 , and therapists can join as well.\nNeurodivergent Family Nights are held 
 on the second Tuesday and fourth Thursday of each month from 5-7 pm (after
  we close to general admission).\nOn these nights\, we dim the lights in t
 he museum\, turn off the sounds\, and offer a limited capacity of 250 gues
 ts. Staff are happy and ready to assist with providing various materials\,
  including noise-cancelling headphones\, fidget toys\, sunglasses\, and we
 ighted materials for your convenience.\nRSVP COMING SOON\n*Registration is
  required and opens two weeks before each event. \nPlay Partners TBD\\n\\
 nMore info: https://www.pretendcity.org/events/neurodivergent-family-night
 -4-2026-05-12/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/neurodivergent-family-night-4-2026-
 05-12/
