CATEGORIES:children,play,toddler,museum,family
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nAges: 0-6
 0 months\\nCategory: Play & Games\\n\\nGet messy. Create together.\nOur im
 mersive summer art exhibit invites families to paint\, sculpt\, build\, an
 d explore without limits. This summer\, art isn&#8217\;t something you loo
 k at—it&#8217\;s something to experience together. Every visit brings so
 mething new\, where creativity grows through art\, movement\, and play.\n1
 0 am &#8211\; 3:30 pm\nThis exhibit is included in museum admission. Spac
 e is limited! Book your tickets now. \nArtists in Action\n\nJune\nSunda
 y\, June 7th &#8211\; Artsy 101 | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nTuesday\, Ju
 ne 9th &#8211\; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nThursday\, J
 une 25th &#8211\; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nSaturday\,
  June 27th &#8211\; Chuck Jones Center for Creativity | Time: 11 AM &#8211
 \; 2 PM\nJuly\nSunday\, July 5th &#8211\; Sawdust Art Festival’s Art Edu
 cation Department | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nTuesday\, July 21st &#8211
 \; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nSaturday\, July 25th &#82
 11\; Chuck Jones Center for Creativity | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 2 PM\nTuesda
 y\, July 28th &#8211\; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\nAugus
 t\nSunday\, August 2nd &#8211\; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 
 PM\nSunday\, August 9th &#8211\; Martin Bruinsma | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12
  PM\nTuesday\, August 18th &#8211\; In-house Artist | Time: 11 AM &#8211\;
  12 PM\nSaturday\, August 22nd &#8211\; Chuck Jones Center for Creativity 
 | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 2 PM\nTuesday\, August 25th &#8211\; In-house Artis
 t | Time: 11 AM &#8211\; 12 PM\n\n\n*Events and dates are subject to chang
 e.\nPretend City Summer Hours\nOpen Tuesday &#8211\; Sunday\n&#8211\;Close
 d on Mondays except Memorial Day and Labor Day\n&#8211\;Closed on Father&#
 8217\;s Day and Fourth of July\n\nFrequently Asked Questions\nIs the summe
 r exhibit included with admission?Yes. The exhibit is included with regula
 r museum admission.\nWill there be special programming?Yes. Additional pro
 gramming and special activities will be announced soon.\nWhat ages is this
  exhibit best for?The exhibit is designed for children ages 2–9 and thei
 r families.\nDo children need art experience to participate?No. This is an
  open-ended\, play-based experience where children can explore creativity 
 at their own pace.\nWill it be messy?Yes. This exhibit encourages hands-on
  creativity\, so we recommend dressing children in clothes that can get me
 ssy.\nAre you open on Mondays?No. Pretend City is closed on Mondays\, exce
 pt for Memorial Day and Labor Day.\nWhy does the exhibit close early?The e
 xhibit closes at 3:30 pm to allow time for cleaning and resetting the spac
 e. The museum remains open until 4:00 pm.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.pret
 endcity.org/events/wonderstudio/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/wonderstudio/
